Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.time

Class Frequency

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.time.Frequency
  • public class Frequency
extends java.lang.Object
    A simple frequency domain object. Frequency is modeled as a Duration per cycle. Static factory methods allow construction of frequencies in terms of cycles per time unit. The start() method begins tracking cycles by returning a Frequency.Cycle object that can be used to determine how long the caller should wait before the next cycle begins (by calling Frequency.Cycle.waitTimeBeforeNextCycle().

    Note

    This object is not thread-safe and cannot be shared.

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
